{"name": "mykurve", "metadata": {"name": "mykurve", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": "https://ddb0515.github.io/mykurve", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": "https://github.com/ddB0515/mykurve", "dependencies": ["attr"], "summary": "Unofficial library to retrieve details of mykurve.com account", "upload_time": 1734553473}, "documentation": ["# mykurve library\n\nUnofficial async library to retrieve details of https://api.mykurve.com/ or https://www.mykurve.com/ account\nThis was done for personal project but feel free to use on your own risk \n\nHope will be useful to someone and if there is any issues (what I think there is...) please open PR or issue will \ntry to help/fix in mean time\n\n## Note\n- This will work only if you don't have 2FA enabled (2FA is still **NOT** supported)\n\n### TODO:\n- handle 2FA \n\n### How to use \n\n```python\nimport asyncio\n\nfrom mykurve import MyKurveApi\nfrom mykurve.data_classes import TimeRange\n\nuserName = \"<your_account>\"\npassword = \"your_password\"\n\nasync def main():\n    api = MyKurveApi()\n    \n    # Get token\n    token = api.get_token(userName, password)\n    print(token)\n\n    # Get account\n    account = api.get_accounts(token.access_token)\n    print(account)\n\n    # Get account info\n    account_info = api.get_account_info(token.access_token, account.accounts[0].accountNumber)\n    print(account_info)\n\n    # Get dashboard\n    dashboard = api.get_dashboard(token.access_token, account.accounts[0].accountNumber)\n    print(dashboard)\n\n    #Get consumption hraph data\n    dashboard = api.get_consumption_graph(token.access_token, account.accounts[0].accountNumber, TimeRange.DAY, 0)\n    print(dashboard)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    loop = asyncio.new_event_loop()\n    asyncio.set_event_loop(loop)\n    try:\n        loop.run_until_complete(main())\n    except KeyboardInterrupt:\n        pass\n    finally:\n        loop.close()\n```\n\nIf you like what I'm doing please support me <br/>\n[![\"Buy Me A Coffee\"](https://www.buymeacoffee.com/assets/img/custom_images/orange_img.png)](https://buymeacoffee.com/ddb0515)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mykurve.const", "documentation": ["Constants for mykurve API"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "mykurve.const.BASE_API_URL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mykurve.const.TOKEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mykurve.const.CUSTOMER_ACCOUNTS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mykurve.const.MY_INFORMATION", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mykurve.const.DASHBOARD", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mykurve.const.CONSUMPTION_GRAPH", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mykurve.const.mykurve_headers", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mykurve.exceptions", "documentation": ["Exceptions."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "mykurve.exceptions.MyKurveApiException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base exception for mykurve API"]}, {"name": "mykurve.exceptions.NotAuthenticated", "bases": ["MyKurveApiException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Not authenticated exception."]}, {"name": "mykurve.exceptions.ApiException", "bases": ["MyKurveApiException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Api error."]}, {"name": "mykurve.exceptions.AuthenticationFailed", "bases": ["MyKurveApiException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Authentication failed."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "mykurve"